! ############################################################ PARAMETER DESCRIPTIONS

RE#    : Reynolds number
PR#    : Prandtl number (* Only meaningful when IHTRANS: 1)
GR#    : Grashof number (* Only meaningful when IHTRANS: 1)
GRDIR  : Gravity direction (0; No gravity (eq. to GR# == 0), 1; -x, 2; -y, 3; -z)
T_INF  : Determine whether initially the solid is cooler or hotter (0; cool, 1; hot)

IRESET : Reset the time to zero (0; not reset, 1; reset)
IREAD  : Read the previous field (0; make initial field, 1; read previous field)
IAVG   : Attain time-averaged field by Reynolds' averaging (0; No avg., 1; avg.)
IPZERO : Initialize the pressure (0; P=0, 1; No change P)
EPS_PTR: Add the random perturbation to the initial field (0.; No perturb. ~ 1.; Full perturb.)
UDRV_I : Target bulk velocity (if ICH=1, CFR) OR fixed mean pressure gradient dP/dx (if ICH=2, CPG)

NEND   : End time steps for calculation (simulation stops at whichever comes first: NEND or TEND)
NPRINT : Time steps for writing instantaneous field
NPRIAVG: Time steps for writing time-avg. field (* Only meaningful when IAVG: 1)
NPIN   : Time steps for writing time history

TEND   : End simulation time (simulation stops at whichever comes first: NEND or TEND)
PTB_TST: Time to start adding perturbation
AVG_TST: Time to start field averaging (* Only meaningful when IAVG: 1) and CD time-averaging

IDTOPT : Time-delta option (0; DT const., 1; CFL const.)
DT_SIZE: Time step size (* Only meaningful when IDTOPT: 0)
CFLFAC : Maximum CFL# criterion (* Only meaningful when IDTOPT: 1)

RESID1 : Residue criteria for solving Poisson eqn. of the pseudo-pressure(PHI) by iterative method
NLEV   : # of multigrid level for poisson eq.
NBLI   : # of iteration at the lowest multigrid level
MGITR  : Maximum iteration # to solve Poisson eqn.
IOLDV  : Initial PHI setting (0; Initialize PHI, 1; Use the previous solution)
IMGSOR : Determine the boundary between the multigrid(MG) method & overrelaxation(SOR) method regions
WWSOR  : Overrelaxation acceleration factor for the SOR method

ILES   : Activate SGS term for large eddy simultaion (0; Deactivate (reduces to DNS), 1; Activate) 
INSMDL : SGS turbulent stress model (1; Vreman's SGS Turbulence Closure)
ITEMDL : SGS heat flux model        (0; Moin's Linear Eddy Diffusivity)
IDVMON : Dynamic CSGS determination with Germano identity model (0; Off, 1; On)
CSGSTS : SGS_TS (turbulent stress) coefficient (* Only meaningful when IDVMON: 0)
CSGSHF : SGS_HF (heat flux) coefficient        (* Only meaningful when IDVMON: 0)
FILTER : SGS FILTERING (1; X, 2; Z, 3; XZ)

IBMON  : Immersed boundary method (0; Deactivate, 1; Activate)
MASSON : Mass source/sink correction (0; Deactivate, 1; Activate)
IMOVING: Moving-body method (0; Deactivate, 1; Activate) 
IHTRANS: Conjugated heat transfer equation (0; Deactivate, 1; Activate)

FILES  : 
 -> Line 1; grid.dat (MANDATORY)
 -> Line 2; previous field file (* Only meaningful when IREAD: 1)

TRACE  : Trace for u, v, w, and p at tracking points
NTR    : Time steps for writing tracking points data
(EXAMPLE)
TRACE   NTR
5       2        [5 POSITION, EVERY 2 TIME STEP WRITE]
5    30   40     1st tracking point's [I,J,K]                   
10   60   80     2nd tracking point's [I,J,K]
15   90   10     3rd tracking point's [I,J,K]
20   120  20     4th tracking point's [I,J,K] 
25   150  100    5th tracking point's [I,J,K]

